cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with predicting conversion rates in display advertising using a nonparametric delayed feedback model. The paper proposes a model that represents the distribution of the time delay without assuming a parametric distribution, which is a machine learning problem and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the interests of users, which is related to information retrieval, and hence, it can also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper proposes a model that represents the distribution of the time delay depending on the content of an ad and the features of a user, which is related to artificial intelligence and can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the distribution of the time delay, which is a statistical problem and can be categorized under cs.SI (Statistics). Finally, the paper deals with predicting conversion rates, which is a data science problem and can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Science).
